  "definitions": [
    {
      "source": "EAS",
      "text": "Firm, a descendant of Cush, the son of Ham. He was the first who claimed to be a “mighty one in the earth.” Babel was the beginning of his kingdom, which he gradually enlarged (Gen. 10:8-10). The “land of Nimrod” (Micah 5:6) is a designation of Assyria or of Shinar, which is a part of it.",
      "extracted_refs": [
        {
          "book": "Genesis",
          "chapter": 10,
          "verses": [
            8,
            9,
            10
          ],
          "verse_count": 3,
