          "verse_count": 1,
          "testament": "OT",
          "raw": "Micah 5:6",
          "source": "EAS"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "(rebellion; or the valiant), a son of Cush and grandson of Ham. The events of his life are recorded in (Genesis 10:8) ff., from which we learn (1) that he was a Cushite; (2) that he established an empire in Shinar (the classical Babylonia) the chief towns being Babel, Erech, Accad and Calneh; and (3) that he extended this empire northward along the course of the Tigris over Assyria, where he founded a second group of capitals, Nineveh, Rehoboth, Calah and Resen.",
